{"_id":"48ee81de-3692-3a05-9f1b-42ba5de38950","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"ad2250182ff26a84dda974e50cd94382","message":"Yes, use ObservableCollection<t>.\r\n\r\nNotifyTaskCompletion is really just an INotifyPropertyChanged wrapper for Task<t>. If that T changes, then it needs to support INotifyPropertyChanged or INotifyCollectionChanged itself.\r\n\r\nSo, if the collection changes after it has been retrieved, the proper type is NotifyTaskCompletion<observablecollection<t>>.","postId":"2014_04_announcement-msdn-async-mvvm-articles-b2165e1d-7e99-386d-b481-ed64583f3ab7","replyTo":"bce6b01a-a648-3751-96ea-3dc54c1438a2","date":"2015-04-08T11:51:45Z","timestamp":1428493905,"authorUserId":"disqus:stephen_cleary"}